<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="90" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,773,2077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,612,1695,1722]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Distribution, habitat, and ecology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[640,860,1695,1721]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Maxillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyhalae">
<emphasis box="[640,860,1695,1721]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Maxillaria pyhalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from three localities (
<emphasis box="[1305,1339,1696,1721]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">i.e.</emphasis>
Regional Conservation Area Amaru-Chihuana, Velapaccha, and Roble) in the district of Huachocolpa, department of 
<collectingRegion box="[136,291,1766,1792]" country="Peru" name="Huancavelica" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Huancavelica</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[303,354,1767,1793]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[371,440,1766,1793]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,2001,2023]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,833,1965]" captionTargetId="figure-320@5.[151,1436,821,1977]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Geographical locations of Maxillaria bicentenaria (squares) and M. pyhalae (triangles) in Peru. Names in capital letters indicate political departments and names associated to red dots indicate provincial capitals. Colour scale indicates elevation." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453892/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Collantes, B." box="[453,628,1766,1793]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" refId="ref5956" refString="Collantes, B. (2014) Huancavelica: Amaru, paraiso de orquideas. Impresso Grafica S. A., Lima, 340 pp." type="book" year="2014">Collantes 2014</bibRefCitation>
). The species is locally abundant and can be found at elevations between 2300 and 
<quantity box="[246,334,1802,1828]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" unit="m" value="2900.0">2900 m</quantity>
. They grow in humid and shaded undergrowth on rocks, but may also be found as epiphytes.
</paragraph>
