<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1130,1405]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,1130,1156]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">Comments:</emphasis>
—Besides the new taxon proposed herein, we believe 
<taxonomicName box="[934,1060,1130,1156]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Maxillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyhalae">
<emphasis box="[934,1060,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">M. pyhalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Reichenbach (1886: 616)" authorityName="Reichenbach" authorityPageNumber="616" authorityYear="1886" box="[136,623,1166,1193]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Maxillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fucata">
<emphasis box="[136,332,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">Maxillaria fucata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Reichenbach, H. G." box="[339,623,1166,1193]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" pagination="616" refId="ref6570" refString="Reichenbach, H. G. (1886) New garden plants. The Gardeners' chronicle: a weekly illustrated journal of horticulture and allied subjects, new series 26: 616." type="book chapter" year="1886">Reichenbach (1886: 616)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, rather than 
<taxonomicName authority="R. H. Pearson (1913: 258)" authorityName="R. H. Pearson" authorityPageNumber="258" authorityYear="1913" box="[761,1314,1166,1193]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Maxillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fletcheriana">
<emphasis box="[761,1022,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">Maxillaria fletcheriana</emphasis>
R.H. Pearson (1913: 258)
</taxonomicName>
(a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rolfe [1922: 25]" authorityName="Rolfe, Bull. Misc. Inform. Kew" authorityPageNumber="25" authorityYear="1922" box="[166,483,1201,1228]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Maxillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis box="[166,189,1202,1227]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[203,290,1202,1227]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">insignis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rolfe, R. A." box="[297,483,1201,1228]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" pagination="22 - 26" refId="ref6638" refString="Rolfe, R. A. (1922) New orchids: decas XLIX. Bulletin of miscellaneous information 1922: 22 - 26. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4118619" type="journal article" year="1922">Rolfe [1922: 25]</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) as suggested by Bennet &amp; Christenson [2001] in the protologue. The line drawings of 
<taxonomicName box="[136,261,1237,1263]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Maxillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyhalae">
<emphasis box="[136,261,1237,1263]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">M. pyhalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
published in the IOP misrepresents important details of the plant specimens, especially the labellum, which makes the identification of this taxon challenging at times. The labellum shape is also not described in detail in the protologue. This has caused confusion with regard to the identity and correct interpretation of this taxon. Additionally, it has been determined that the 
<typeStatus box="[491,589,1343,1369]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">holotype</typeStatus>
and an isotype of 
<taxonomicName box="[799,912,1343,1370]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Maxillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phylae">
<emphasis box="[799,822,1344,1369]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[837,912,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">phylae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are gathered at MOL under the same collection number (i.e. 
<emphasis box="[279,461,1378,1405]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">León et al. 2975</emphasis>
, MO; 
<bibRefCitation author="Trujillo, D." box="[534,687,1378,1405]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref6905" refString="Trujillo, D. (2014) Annotated list of orchidaceae types of the Bennett collection at the forestry herbarium MOL. Lankesteriana 14: 1 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.15517 / lank. v 14 i 1.15584" type="journal article" year="2014">Trujillo 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
